text:
Premier League’s top five scoring duos in all competitions By Adam Smith Last Updated: 23/02/17 10:38am Which Premier League partnerships have created the most goals in all competitions? 
Five duos from four different top-flight clubs have all notched five goals between them so far, according to transfermarkt.co.uk . 
It's good news for Manchester United ahead of their EFL Cup final against Southampton on Sunday, live on Sky Sports 1 from 3.45pm, with two partnerships featuring in the top five. Man Utd vs So'ton 
Interestingly, Everton's Romelu Lukaku has scored four goals from Yannick Bolasie assists - despite Bolasie being sidelined with a knee injury since early December. Everton's Yannick Bolasie has been sidelined with a knee injury since December 
Tottenham's Christian Eriksen also misses out on the top five partnerships, but the Dane has assisted Harry Kane and Dele Alli four times each, and has set up another four for Heung-min Son. Christian Eriksen misses out but has assisted Harry Kane and Dele Alli with four goals each and another three for Heung-Min Son 
Chelsea's Cesc Fabregas has spent most of this season on the bench but has still teed up three goals for Gary Cahill this term. 
Flip the cards below to reveal the top five goal-scoring duos...
